    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-10-31</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-11-21T21:59:48Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Children's Chemical Risk Reduction Act - Requires any children's product or child care article that contains a phthalate to be treated as a banned hazardous substance under the Federal Hazardous Substances Act. Applies certain prohibitions of that Act to such product article.</p> <p>Provides that, if a manufacturer modifies a children's product or child care article that contains a phthalate to comply with such ban, it shall: (1) use an alternative to phthalates that is the least toxic; and (2) not use any of specified prohibited alternatives to phthalates.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Children's Chemical Risk Reduction Act</title>
    <titles>
